When the empty cylinder is filled with saturated steam at 100 psia, the steam inside will reach **thermal equilibrium** with the reservoir, meaning it will be at the **same temperature** as the saturated steam in the pipe (since pressure remains constant at 100 psia). The steam will remain **saturated** (not subcooled or superheated) unless additional heat is added or removed. Thus, **Option C** is the most accurate.
